# Code commenting standards

Scope: **source and test code** — not `docs/*.md` (see [documentation-standards.mdc](./documentation-standards.mdc)).

## JSDoc (exported symbols)

All exported functions, classes, and public methods MUST have JSDoc:

- `@param` with type and purpose
- `@returns` when not void
- `@throws` when applicable
- Brief description of behavior (not a restatement of the name)

## Inline comments

- Explain **why**, not what the code already says.
- Use `// TODO:`, `// NOTE:`, `// FIXME:` for coordination — include ticket or context when known.
- Avoid redundant comments (`// increment i`).

## ESLint

Public exports should satisfy documentation lint rules. Do not disable ESLint for missing docs unless there is a documented exception.

## AI role

When generating or refactoring exported APIs, add or update JSDoc in the same change.
